   <mods:abstract>Does not doubt that John Jay has had great anxieties. All Adams had were
            unnecessary but are now past. Would like to have a free conversation with Jay on the
            subjects mentioned. But things move slowly here. John Adams does not think he should go
            to Paris until the English representative has full power to treat with America as an
            independent nation. If all American ministers were there, peace would seem likely and
            another loan for England would be concluded. Has no confidence in Shelburne's sincerity.
            "They are only amusing us." Wants to know all steps taken however. Spain short sighted
            in not making a treaty with us. France should have great weight with America and
            Holland. America will have to tie herself more closely to France if the neutral powers
            are more friendly with England. If America admitted to armed neutrality, she would be
            freer of France. We are tied to France by her aid.</mods:abstract>
